{"_id":"00c5a316-5eec-4d27-b682-8a82ef8758f8","type":"ability","name":"Always Aware","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Always Aware","rank":"1","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"You can always use your Wilderness Survival skill when rolling initiative.","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"0541920c-16f9-4403-8442-ec2b318b737c","type":"ability","name":"Tracker","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Tracker","rank":"1","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"1","description":"You may use this ability when you find fresh (within 24 hours) signs such as a trail, scat, spoor, or other signs left by a creature in wilderness. You learn the direction and speed of travel, and you gain a Boon on checks made to identify and track the creature for the next hour.","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"27a30e91-084f-4075-bb24-f2fe0af89f49","type":"ability","name":"Fight or Flight","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Fight or Flight","rank":"3","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"When you enter combat, you immediately regain 2 Vim and Vigour if they are not already at maximum.","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"357e9de5-2d1e-42b4-bb30-bb6f7cf29bdd","type":"ability","name":"Lay of the Land","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Lay of the Land","rank":"1","type":"activity","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"1","description":"You spend an hour looking around an area up to a few square kilometers (ten square kilometers if you spend a full day). You get to know the major landmarks, sources of food and water, likely areas for shelter, likely ambush locations, and other similar information. If you are looking for specific information, the GM may present it to you upon a sucessful roll.","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"3a1a1c98-8f41-48f2-89f3-e49245866385","type":"ability","name":"Alpha Instinct","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Alpha Instinct","rank":"3","type":"technique","action":"","defense":"intuition","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"2","description":"When you would apply a wound to a wild animal, you may use this technique to attempt to instead have it flee. You may use this a maximum of once per round. Particularly enraged creatures (or, for example, creatures defending their young) may be immune, in which case the GM should provide you with a possible method for calming the creature or causing it to flee instead (for example, its young are in a den nearby, if you back away slowly it will calm).","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"6254920e-ed5a-4d65-a0d1-d28e81985a08","type":"ability","name":"Quick Trap","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Quick Trap","rank":"1","type":"technique","action":"slow","defense":"intuition/agility/strength","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"1","description":"You set up a basic trap. Choose an effect: Standard Agility damage, Prone, Slowed, or Dazed. The next time a creature passes by the trap you make a Wilderness check vs Intuition (if it does not see the trap), Agility (if it tries to avoid it), or Strength (if it sees the trap and does not try to avoid it). On a success, the creature takes the effect you chose, and its movement is stopped. You may have a number of active traps equal to your Wilderness ranks.","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vigour","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"666567f9-8fea-4e0f-8abe-ab81752a5f4c","type":"ability","name":"Improved Traps","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Improved Traps","rank":"3","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"You must have the Quick Trap ability to select this. When you use Quick Trap, you may spend an additional 1 Vigour to select two effects or to make it deal Heavy Agility damage instead.","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"7a52f66f-0312-4e1b-b0be-b90346c89f6c","type":"ability","name":"Poisoned Trap","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Poisoned Trap","rank":"5","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"You must have the Quick Trap ability to select this. When you use Quick Trap, you may spend an additional 1 Vigour to apply a poison to it from your inventory. The poison can be recovered if the trap fails or is not activated.","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"7e373bfc-0e02-4e0c-9bfd-cf2c210f0ce7","type":"ability","name":"One With the Wild","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"One With the Wild","rank":"5","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"You ignore additional movement costs of terrain effects while in wilderness areas. While in wilderness areas, all strength, and agility based checks have a boon.","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"81e3e195-ff7f-4429-aa55-631dbc999052","type":"ability","name":"Forage","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Forage","rank":"1","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"1","description":"While spending at least an hour moving through any wilderness area, you may use this to gather enough food to feed yourself without spending additional time to do so.","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"854380d8-315a-4f61-b66a-7008850f3fb3","type":"ability","name":"Sixth Sense","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Sixth Sense","rank":"5","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"You can track creatures even over stone and through cities so long as you start from a place you are certain the creature was. The trail still runs cold after 24 hours.","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"a8228581-ccb9-4840-b352-0139234bd8d7","type":"ability","name":"Scout","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill":"Wilderness Survival","name":"Scout","rank":"3","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"You may use your Wilderness skill to hide or move quietly in wild areas.","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"","skill_id":"wilderness_survival"}}
{"_id":"ec2705a5-efed-422a-bc91-41140b48f7b0","type":"skill","name":"Wilderness Survival","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/wilderness_survival.svg","system":{"skill_id":"wilderness_survival","domain":"Expertise","rank":1,"stat":"intuition","description":"This skill is used for navigating and surviving in wild areas, including finding food, shelter, and water, setting up traps, tracking, and practical knowledge of flora and fauna."}}
